  "texts": [
    "This confirms the significance of the Q index, indicating heterogeneity in the effect size across the studies.",
    "The value of I 2 value is also 47.24%, indicating a moderate level of heterogeneity [49].",
    "Meta-regression analysisThe effect sizes obtained from the random effects model were not found to be statistically significant for gender, age, sample size, duration of intervention, and type of cognitive disorders (P > 0.05) (Table 2).",
    "This means that these variables did not have a great impact on the results of studies related to the improvement of cognitive disorders through virtual reality.",
    "However, the effect size obtained from the random effects model for the type of VR intervention was statistically significant (P = 0.047)."
  ]
